cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for crowd monitoring and management, specifically focusing on crowd counting and density map estimation in aerial and ground imagery. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new neural network architecture for this task, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep learning techniques and the evaluation on benchmark datasets suggest that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the application of these techniques to crowd management and surveillance could also fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
